Class SteepestDescentOptimiser

  • java.lang.Object
    • pulse.util.UpwardsNavigable

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Descriptive, Reflexive
    public class SteepestDescentOptimiser
extends PathOptimiser
    The simplest possible PathSolver, which assumes that the minimum direction coincides with the inverted gradient. Used in combination with the GoldenSectionSolver for increased accuracy.
    See Also:
    GoldenSectionOptimiser, Wikipedia page

      • direction

        public Vector direction​(Path p)

        The direction of the minimum at the iteration k is calculated simply as the the inverted gradient vector: pk = -gk. Invokes p.setDirection().
